  "text": "It is widely known that noise over PLs remains the most detrimental element influencing communication signals and is, generally, classified into two categories: background noise and impulsive noise, with the latter being the most dominant one which is characterized by high amplitude, short duration, and random probability of occurrence. Numerous methods have been introduced in the literature to diminish the adverse effect of impulsive noise; the most common of which is the application of a nonlinear preprocessor, such as blanking, at the receiver front-end to zero the incoming signal samples that exceed a certain threshold [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] .",
